article.description: Siebert, Pierre lead Dayton past St. Bonaventure 75-61
article.headline: Siebert, Pierre lead Dayton past St. Bonaventure 75-61
article.linkText: Siebert, Pierre lead Dayton past St. Bonaventure 75-61
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Jordan Sibert scored 24 points, Dyshawn Pierre had 15 points and 13 rebounds and Dayton remained part of the log jam atop the Atlantic 10 standings with a 75-61 win over St. Bonaventure on Saturday. Kyle Davis hit 5 of 6 shots and had 13 points for the Flyers (19-5, 9-3), who shot 51 percent to win its 18th straight at home. Youssou Ndoye had 16 points and 12 rebounds for the Bonnies (13-10, 6-6), who were without standout freshman point guard Jaylen Adams. Adams, who has started every game and averages 10 points, is out indefinitely after surgery to repair a fracture/dislocation in the ring finger of his right hand. He has 63 assists and 15 turnovers in league play. Without Adams, the Bonnies had 17 turnovers to just six assists. His replacement, Iakeem Alston had 11 points, three assists and three turnovers. The Bonnies shot 49 percent but went 0-11 from 3-point range.
